org.cougaar.planning.ldm.asset
Interface Null_PG

All Superinterfaces:
LockedPG
All Known Implementing Classes:
ClusterPG.Null_ClusterPG, CommunityPG.Null_CommunityPG, EntityPG.Null_EntityPG, ItemIdentificationPG.Null_ItemIdentificationPG, LocationSchedulePG.Null_LocationSchedulePG, RelationshipPG.Null_RelationshipPG, TypeIdentificationPG.Null_TypeIdentificationPG
public interface Null_PG
extends LockedPG

marker class for indicating that a PG is unlikely to ever be filled. The "null" version of a PG is available only via the static data member WhateverPG.nullPG, where WhateverPG is the base PG interface. If an Asset has an actual null as the value for a given PG, it is interpreted as unspecified , and potentially available for late-binding. A value of a Null_PG instance prevents late-binding, activation. All accessors will throw an UndefinedValueException if called.
